svaha-kit

This directory is the Svaha kit distribution — the engine, not a user continuity system.
The loop refuses to boot, mint a _NEXT, stamp occupancy, or /init here: this is the
kit-as-system-dir guard (v0.6.2). Run the loop inside your OWN project instead —
/init there once, then svaha. The kit's own development continuity lives in its git
history (and ledger/CHANGELOG.md for structural changes), never in a _NEXT loop here.

Presence of this file is the signal; the continuity writers (bin/next-write.sh,
next-boot.sh, next-consume.sh), /init, and coherence-check.py all key off it.
